Photo by Igor Jones on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1. Waking Up Late Get a headstart with your day by waking up early. Create a strong morning routine and be at your maximum productivity. 2. Poor Hygiene It will negatively affect your ability to network with people who may help you to be successful.'.

Photo by Igor Jones on August 30, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '3. Not Taking Accountability For Your Failures Although your success can be affected by your circumstances, 90% of your success relies on YOU. 4. Thinking others Should Help You Nobody owes you anything. Nobody will solve your problems for you. You must take charge of your life and don't blame others.'.

Photo by Igor Jones on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5. Watching Too Much Netflix or TV This type of escapism can take hours of your day. Hours that should have been spent on things that could bring you closer to your goals. 6. Being Too Consumed With Sports It might be entertaining, but it only benefits the players and not you.'.

Photo by Igor Jones on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7. Having No Savings If you don't have an emergency fund, then your properties are always in danger of liquidation, or you may need loans. 8. Surrounding Yourself With Poor People You are the sum of the five people you spend the most time with. Poor people will reinforce your poor habits and beliefs.'.

Photo by Igor Jones on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '9. Eating Junk And Fast Food It makes you feel sluggish at work and clouds your judgment. Be careful of what you take in. Food has a direct effect on how your body and mind function. 10. Not Following Through With Your Goals Take action and strategically think out your plan. It's not enough to have dreams. You must also put in the work.'.
